&gt; aren't ever going to be interested in much in grand plots and 
&gt; rping storylines. I certainly hope such things could make them 
&gt; see more depth in EQ, but I am skeptical. 

&gt; I think you'll find the majority of people who left the pvp in 
&gt; disgust are much more interest in that old militia idea or some 
&gt; sort of rp-pvp switch. Not so much because they fear getting 
&gt; killed, but is seems obvious such tools are needed to make the 
&gt; game resemble the EQ we all love. 

&gt; I've been flamed for it before here, I'll say it again:) The 
&gt; attitude of most pvps is that if &quot;you don't like it then 
&gt; leave&quot;. PVP's expect everyone to conform to their 
&gt; powergaming style, they never once think to maybe give a little 
&gt; back to the game in hopes of making pvp better and maybe even 
&gt; something more interesting than it was in UO.Oh well with the 
&gt; current attitude, its becoming the same UO style of pvp and I 
&gt; and most have met are bored to tears with it. 

&gt; In short I think you are preaching to the wrong crowd, but I 
&gt; hope you can promote some change. 

&gt; Chris praying for another switch option 
